COVID-19 test JOHANNESBURG - The health department reported 1,622 new COVID-19 cases in South Africa in the last 24 hours. This brings the total number of cases to 715,868. READ: Mkhize warns COVID-19 battle is not over There have been 24 additional COVID-19 deaths recorded, although only 5 of these occurred in the past 48 hours. South Africa's COVID-19 death toll has increased to 18,968. Recoveries currently stand at 646,170, which translates to a 90.3% recovery rate. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. COVID-19